==Latin==

===Etymology===
From {{term|ne||not|lang=la}} + {{term|ūllus||any|lang=la}}, literally meaning "not any".

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|Classical}} {{IPA|/ˈnuːl.lus/|lang=la}}
* {{audio|la-cls-nullus.ogg|Audio (Classical)}}

===Determiner===
{{la-adj-1&2|nūllus|nulla|nūlla|nullum|nūllum}}

# [[no one]], [[no]], [[not]] [[any]]
#: '''''Nūllum''' amat.''
#:: He loves no one.

